What is the simplest form of $3\dfrac{8}{12}$?
(A) 3\dfrac{3}{4}
(B) \frac{42}{12}
(C) \frac{10}{3}
(D) 3\dfrac{2}{3}

Choose the answer in the simplest form.  $$\frac{9}{4}\times \frac{8}{27}=$$．
(A) \frac{72}{108}
(B) \frac{18}{27}
(C) \frac{8}{12}
(D) \frac{2}{3}

A recipe that makes~$5$~servings of hot chocolate requires~$2$~squares of chocolate,~$\dfrac{1}{4}$~cup sugar,~$1$~cup water and~$4$~cups milk. Jordan has~$5$~squares of chocolate,~$2$~cups of sugar, lots of water, and~$7$~cups of milk. If he maintains the same ratio of ingredients, what is the greatest number of servings of hot chocolate he can make?
(A) 5\dfrac{1}{8}
(B) 6\dfrac{1}{4}
(C) 7\dfrac{1}{2}
(D) 8\dfrac{3}{4}
(E) 9\dfrac{7}{8}

Convert the decimal $$0.65$$ to a fraction in its simplest form.
(A) \dfrac{13}{20}
(B) \dfrac{3}{4}
(C) \dfrac{17}{20}
(D) \dfrac{6}{5}

What is the simplest form of $\frac{15}{20}$?
(A) \frac{4}{5}
(B) \frac{3}{4}
(C) \frac{2}{3}
(D) \frac{15}{20}

The sum of the repeating decimals~$0.\overline{163}$~and~$0.\overline{614}$~is ．
(A) 0.7
(B) \dfrac{777}{1000}
(C) 1
(D) \dfrac{7}{9}

Which of the following is the largest fraction?
(A) \dfrac{3}{5}
(B) \dfrac{3}{6}
(C) \dfrac{3}{7}
(D) \dfrac{3}{8}
